Package SkipList

Class SkipListSetItem<T extends Comparable<T>>

java.lang.Object
SkipList.SkipListSetItem<T>
Type Parameters:
T - accepts generics as parameters.
public class SkipListSetItem<T extends Comparable<T>> extends Object
This class provides the SkipList Set with data elements. Each instance of the SkipListSetItem class store the data value of the element, as well as the location of it neighbor.
Since:
July 27, 2023
Version:
1.0
Author:
Gradi Tshielekeja Mbuyi

  • Constructor Details

    • SkipListSetItem

      public SkipListSetItem()
      The default constructor takes in no parameters and is called in the beginning of the set's initialization. Given an empty set, SkipListSetItem() is called to initialize the head of the set, where each value and neighbor are set to NULL.

    • SkipListSetItem

      public SkipListSetItem(T value)
      The secondary constructor is called during the add operation. Given a value V and a set S, SkipListSetItem(T value) is called to allocate space for a new element. Upon allocating space, value V is added to the given set S.
      Parameters:
      value - given value whose element is to be added in the collection

      public int compareTo(T value)
